original: Germans like myself have autism levels that are altogether too high for Catholicism and Orthodoxy so needed Protestantism a la Martin Luther so we could go do our own thing. Anglicanism after the Restoration of the English Monarchy and the full embracement of the Royal Society seems like the perfect doctrine to somebody like myself. Too bad we had to have ourselves an (((enlightenment))) and ruin it.
translated: الألمان مثلي لديهم مستويات من التوحد مرتفعة جدًا بالنسبة للكاثوليكية والأرثوذكسية، لذا كانوا بحاجة إلى البروتستانتية على غرار مارتن لوثر حتى نتمكن من القيام بأشياءنا الخاصة. تبدو الأنجليكانية بعد استعادة الملكية الإنجليزية والاحتضان الكامل للجمعية الملكية بمثابة العقيدة المثالية لشخص مثلي. من المؤسف أنه كان علينا أن نحصل على ((التنوير))) وندمره.

original: Germans like myself have autism levels that are altogether too high for Catholicism and Orthodoxy so needed Protestantism a la Martin Luther so we could go do our own thing. Too bad we had to have ourselves an (((enlightenment))) and ruin it.
translated: 像我这样的德国人的自闭症水平对于天主教和东正教来说太高了，所以需要像马丁·路德那样的新教，这样我们就可以去做自己的事情。英国君主制复辟后的英国国教和皇家学会的全面拥护对于像我这样的人来说似乎是完美的教义。太糟糕了，我们不得不拥有一个（（（启蒙）））并毁掉它。

L'anglicanisme après la restauration de la monarchie anglaise et l'adhésion totale à la Royal Society semble être la doctrine parfaite pour quelqu'un comme moi. Dommage que nous ayons dû nous procurer une (((illumination))) et la gâcher.

original: "I was only a three year old girl when I was already attacked by a tall man with my parents present. I have no use for them and am perpetually angry at the society which had a chance to keep them away from us decent people. In general, criminals are loud, brazen, they have a short wild temper, they are demanding and haughty and do not take well to rejection. As long as they are allowed to be anywhere near hardworking citizens...Society has a stigma and will never be fully peaceful. "
translated: "كنت فتاة في الثالثة من عمري فقط عندما تعرضت لهجوم من قبل رجل طويل القامة وكان والدي حاضرين. ليس لدي أي فائدة لهم وأنا غاضبة دائمًا من المجتمع الذي أتيحت له الفرصة لإبعادهم عنا نحن الأشخاص المحترمين. بشكل عام، المجرمون صاخبون، وقحون، لديهم مزاج جامح قصير، وهم متطلبون ومتغطرسون ولا يتقبلون الرفض جيدًا. طالما أنه يُسمح لهم بالتواجد في أي مكان بالقرب من المواطنين المجتهدين... المجتمع لديه وصمة عار ولن تفعل ذلك أبدًا كن سلميًا تمامًا."

original: "I was only a three year old girl when I was already attacked by a tall man with my parents present. I have no use for them and am perpetually angry at the society which had a chance to keep them away from us decent people. In general, criminals are loud, brazen, they have a short wild temper, they are demanding and haughty and do not take well to rejection. As long as they are allowed to be anywhere near hardworking citizens...Society has a stigma and will never be fully peaceful. "
translated: “当我只有三岁的时候，我就已经在父母在场的情况下被一个高个子男人袭击了。我对他们毫无用处，并且对社会永远感到愤怒，因为社会有机会让他们远离我们正派的人。一般来说，犯罪分子吵闹、厚颜无耻、脾气暴躁、要求高、傲慢，不接受拒绝。只要允许他们接近勤劳的公民……社会就有耻辱，永远不会完全平静。”

original: "I was only a three year old girl when I was already attacked by a tall man with my parents present. I have no use for them and am perpetually angry at the society which had a chance to keep them away from us decent people. In general, criminals are loud, brazen, they have a short wild temper, they are demanding and haughty and do not take well to rejection. As long as they are allowed to be anywhere near hardworking citizens...Society has a stigma and will never be fully peaceful. "
translated: "Je n'avais que trois ans quand j'ai déjà été attaquée par un homme de grande taille en présence de mes parents. Je n'ai aucune utilité pour eux et je suis perpétuellement en colère contre la société qui a eu la chance de les éloigner de nous, les honnêtes gens. En général, les criminels sont bruyants, effrontés, ils ont un tempérament court et sauvage, ils sont exigeants et hautains et n'acceptent pas bien le rejet. Tant qu'ils sont autorisés à se trouver à proximité de citoyens qui travaillent dur... La société est stigmatisée et ne le fera jamais. être pleinement en paix. »

original: "I was only a three year old girl when I was already attacked by a tall man with my parents present. I have no use for them and am perpetually angry at the society which had a chance to keep them away from us decent people. In general, criminals are loud, brazen, they have a short wild temper, they are demanding and haughty and do not take well to rejection. As long as they are allowed to be anywhere near hardworking citizens...Society has a stigma and will never be fully peaceful. "
translated: „Ich war erst ein dreijähriges Mädchen, als ich in Anwesenheit meiner Eltern bereits von einem großen Mann angegriffen wurde. Ich habe keine Verwendung für sie und bin ständig wütend auf die Gesellschaft, die die Chance hatte, sie von uns anständigen Menschen fernzuhalten Im Allgemeinen sind Kriminelle laut, dreist, sie haben ein kurzes, wildes Temperament, sie sind anspruchsvoll und hochmütig und vertragen keine Ablehnung. Solange es ihnen erlaubt ist, auch nur annähernd in der Nähe von fleißigen Bürgern zu sein ... Die Gesellschaft hat ein Stigma und wird es niemals tun Sei vollkommen friedlich.“

original: "I was only a three year old girl when I was already attacked by a tall man with my parents present. In general, criminals are loud, brazen, they have a short wild temper, they are demanding and haughty and do not take well to rejection. As long as they are allowed to be anywhere near hardworking citizens...Society has a stigma and will never be fully peaceful. "
translated: "मैं केवल तीन साल की बच्ची थी जब मेरे माता-पिता के साथ एक लंबे आदमी ने मुझ पर हमला कर दिया था। मुझे उनके लिए कोई फायदा नहीं है और मैं हमेशा उस समाज से नाराज रहती हूं जिसने उन्हें हम सभ्य लोगों से दूर रखने का मौका दिया। सामान्य तौर पर, अपराधी बड़बोले, बेशर्म होते हैं, उनका स्वभाव छोटा और जंगली होता है, वे मांग करने वाले और घमंडी होते हैं और अस्वीकृति को स्वीकार नहीं करते हैं। जब तक उन्हें मेहनती नागरिकों के करीब रहने की अनुमति दी जाती है... समाज पर एक कलंक है और ऐसा कभी नहीं होगा पूरी तरह शांतिपूर्ण रहें।"

original: "I was only a three year old girl when I was already attacked by a tall man with my parents present. I have no use for them and am perpetually angry at the society which had a chance to keep them away from us decent people. In general, criminals are loud, brazen, they have a short wild temper, they are demanding and haughty and do not take well to rejection. As long as they are allowed to be anywhere near hardworking citizens...Society has a stigma and will never be fully peaceful. "
translated: "Yo era sólo una niña de tres años cuando ya fui atacada por un hombre alto en presencia de mis padres. No los necesito y estoy perpetuamente enojada con la sociedad que tuvo la oportunidad de mantenerlos alejados de nosotros, las personas decentes. En general, los criminales son ruidosos, descarados, tienen un temperamento corto y salvaje, son exigentes y altivos y no aceptan bien el rechazo. Siempre y cuando se les permita ser ciudadanos trabajadores... La sociedad tiene un estigma y nunca lo hará. ser completamente pacífico."

original: "I was only a three year old girl when I was already attacked by a tall man with my parents present. In general, criminals are loud, brazen, they have a short wild temper, they are demanding and haughty and do not take well to rejection. As long as they are allowed to be anywhere near hardworking citizens...Society has a stigma and will never be fully peaceful. "
translated: “Eu era uma menina de apenas três anos quando já fui atacada por um homem alto com meus pais presentes. Não tenho utilidade para eles e estou perpetuamente zangada com a sociedade que teve a chance de mantê-los longe de nós, pessoas decentes. Em geral, os criminosos são barulhentos, descarados, têm um temperamento curto e selvagem, são exigentes e arrogantes e não aceitam bem a rejeição. Desde que lhes seja permitido estar perto de cidadãos trabalhadores... A sociedade tem um estigma e nunca o fará. esteja totalmente em paz."

original: They arrive in the United States, not for the American dream, as many politicians both Democrat and Republican, like to say. When asked, most will say they are proud Hondurans or proud Nigerians "“ proud nationals of the country they came from.
translated: إنهم يصلون إلى الولايات المتحدة، ليس من أجل الحلم الأميركي، كما يقول العديد من السياسيين، سواء من الديمقراطيين أو الجمهوريين. إنهم يصلون لاغتصاب اقتصادنا، دون أي نية لاحتضان الثقافة، أو تبني اللغة، أو اعتبار أنفسهم أمريكيين. عندما يُسألون، سيقول معظمهم إنهم فخورون بكونهم هندوراسيين أو نيجيريين فخورين "" مواطنين فخورين بالبلد الذي أتوا منه.

original: They arrive in the United States, not for the American dream, as many politicians both Democrat and Republican, like to say. translated: 正如许多民主党和共和党政客喜欢说的那样，他们来到美国，并不是为了美国梦。他们来到这里是为了篡夺我们的经济，无意拥抱我们的文化、采用我们的语言或认为自己是美国人。当被问及时，大多数人会说他们是自豪的洪都拉斯人或自豪的尼日利亚人“为自己的祖国感到自豪的国民。
